{"/service/ndnp/wyu/batch_wyu_hartville_ver01/data/sn86072160/00514150461/1923110401/0051.xml":{"full_text":"SUNDAY, NOVEMBER 4, 1923\nMIMON BRAKE\nNEAR PERFECT\n\nComplications Elimin\nated in Making Im\nprovements.\nThe Marman Motor Car company\nbelieves that In it\u00ae front wheel\nbrake mechanism, it has attained\nthe peak In four wheel brake\nmechanism, and offers th\u00a9 following\nfeatures of th\u00a9 new Marmon front\nwheel brakes as evidence.\nJ. Simple internal mechanism:\nA remarkable degree of simplicity\nhas been attained in Marmon front\nwheel brake construction. They\nnecessitate few parts and few com\nplications. This means greater de\npendability, lighter weight and\nlonger wearing qualities.\n2. Quiet, simple controls: Per\nhaps the most ingenious single fea\nture of Marmon brakes lies in the\nsimplicity of the control linkage.\nWith ,th\u00ab cross shaft lying within\nAh\u00a9 channel ot th\u00a9 front axle and\nwith all working parts of the brakes\nenclosed within dust proof drums,\nth\u00a9 clean cut appearance of the do\nsign speak.-i for itself in assurance\nof dependability and safety.\n3. All working parts enclosed\nAutomobile brakes are. by their na\nture, placed in a position of maxi\nmu in exposure to dirt, water and\nmud. Working parts must be pro\ntactsd if long wearing qualities an t\nefficient operation are expected. The\nmechanism of the Marmon brake,\nproper, is completely housed within\nthe drum\n4. Simple and permanent adjust\nments: Th\u00a9 right and left brake.-\nare equalized by adjusting the\nlength of the vertical links which\nextend from the cross shaft. Th\u00ab-\nadjustment for tightening the front\nbrakes with relation to the rear ones\nis anode at the forward end of the\nrod which extends from th\u00a9 brake\npedal. Nothing could bo simpler or\nmore effective.\n5. Light foot pressure: Unless\nsome preventive means is provided,\nthe use of four wheel brakes wll\nnecessitate excessive foot pressure\nby the driver, or in lieu of that,\nexcessively long travel of the foot\nThe Marmon design has\nutilized a principle which causes the\nmomentum of the car itself to assist\nthe driver in pressing the brake\nbands against the drums.\nfi. Steering \u2019not encumbered: The\nlinkage which controls the brakes is\nextremely simple, and does not in\nany way hamper the movement oi\nth-* \u2018slfti r.n'f system. Moreover th-:\ndesign, is such that the motion.\nth. wheofs and steering knuckk\nussenmiy does not affect the brnk\ncontrol.\n7. Safety paramount: To furth\nprdmpte safety an adjustment\nproviled to proportion the pre\nof \u2019tli\u00df front brakes to that f\nrear brakes causing the rear win.\nto lock before the front whee\nThis. .of course, becomes imporiaa\nonly jin extreme application of tin\nbrakes and is an example ot the\nthoroughness with which the Mar\nTnon brake has been developed to\nprevelt dangerous skidding unde,\ncxactfhg conditions.\n8. f'ront axle strengthened: As\nmentioned, the front\naxle, Steering knuckles and all re\nlated parts have been greatly\nstrengthened to resist the greater\nstresses imposed by th\u00a9 action of\npowerful brakes.\n9. Unsprung weight maintained\nat minimum: In adding the brake\nmechanism to the front axle, the\ndesign of each part has been care\nfully studied to obtain the greatest\npossible strength from every ounce\nof metal used. Tho result is not\nonly a construction with ample sac\ntors of safety against breakage, but\na comparatively light weight assem\nbly, that insures tho continuation oi\nMarmon roadability, tire economy\nand riding qualities.\nMANY ETeMENTSGO\nINTO THE MAKING OF\nAN AUTOMOBILE TIRE\nThe number of dfferont elements,\nXrr pigments, which are mixed with\nrubber before It is incorporated in\nto automobile tries, probably would\nastound the average motorist. There\nactually is no pure rubber in any\nportion of the casing, although that\npart known os cushion stock ap\nproaches that condition as nearly us\npossible. It is necessary to mix some\nother\u2018substances with it in order to\nmake it vulcanize. The cushion\nztrtsk, that part just beneath the\ntread and in which the breaker strip\nIs Imbedded, is known among tire\nmanufacturers an pur\u00a9 gum stock.\nBut ail th\u00a9 rubber used in other\nparts of the tire ar\u00a9 mixed with on\u00a9\nor more pigments very thoroughly\non mixin- machines. Th\u00a9 proper\ncompounding of rubber for use in\ntire\u00a9 brings about countless hours\nof experimentation. In the cos\u00a9 <jf\nMiller tires for example, several\ncheipists and expert compounders\ndevote practically their entire time\ntoward the perfection of compound\ning methods which are designed to\ngive greater and more satisfactory\n/service to tiro users.\nIn the compounding departments,\nexperts weigh every bit of pigment\nwhich Is to go into certain batches\nof rubber, and weigh them so care\nfully that there is not a variation\nof erven a fraction of an ounce be\ntween any two hatches to be used\nfor th\u00a9 game purpoae.\nHASH LEADS THE WORLD IN MOTOR CAR VALUE\nf\nJEWETT BROUGHAM HANDSOME i\nthree\nTHE Ml I IILT' H OPERATIONS\nNEW JEWETT j\u2014\u00bb \"Wu IbmiTt IN CONSTRVCI\nnUIKs-WbEl: TIOSOF I\nBROUGHAM \u25a0\u2018Aga BODY WHICH\nFINISHED makes\nIN BLACK HISTORY IN\nHIGH BAKED AUTO\nENAMEL INDUSTRY\n-r\nU 3\nI OHt OF THE POIISHINC \u2014..\u2014f*-'- THE BIC HHMLV CONSIBUCTED\nII OPERATIONS AFTER A BAKE BOOH. NOFt FAHEI ISAMU.ED k\nfastening oh the upper back panel ins\nHere ar\u00a9 a few intimate views df the popular 1924 Jewett brougham. Its baked enamel finish and\nwood body construction are features The Jmfrett is represented in Casper by the Le<> Doud Motor Co.\nBUSINESS OUTLOOK IS BRIGHT,\nNASH CASPER DEALER STATES\nBY P. N. TARR.\nAfter passing through one of the\nmost successful years in tho history\nof the industry, the business outlook\nn motor car manufacture for the\near 1924 looms exceedingly bright.\nVs a basis for this prediction on my\npart, I would point to tho genera\u2019,\nhealthy condition of all industries\nvhich are mor\u00a9 or loss directly linlo\nwith that of automobile manu\nfacture, such as mines, steel and\number mills, and others engaged in\nProducing raw materials. Further\nnore. there is a closer relatiutiship\n-etwoen capital and labor than \u00a9ver\nbefore.\nAnother Important factor is th\u00a9\nnoticeable improvement in distribu\ntion methods. The manufacturers\nhrough their distributors, are lend\nng assistance to their dealer orgun\nzations in various ways not hereto\nfore considered feasible, with the re\nsult that there Is a closer spirit of\n-o-operatlon and harmony between\n\u2022nnnufacturer anil dealer. With this\n'eellng of security thus established,\nhe dealer is better equipped to go\n428 South Elm Street\nPennsylvania Vacuum Cup Tires\nPresto-lite Batteries THE\nLIBERTY\n983 Goodrich Silvertown Cords GARAGE\nTHE r\nLIBERTY Expert Repaiiw S\nGARAGE Prest-o-lite Service\nANNEX\n\u201cStrictly for Passenger Cars\u201d Truck and Passenger Car Storage A\n414 South Elm Street\nout after business. He puts pep and\nenthusiasm into his work, and is\nable to serve th\u00a9 automobile buying\npublic better. Tho result is more\nand better sales.\nTh\u00a9 greatest difficulty the local\ndealer finds to contend with today,\nI however, is tho \u201cused car\u201d problem,\ni This is indeed a bugbear to the\nwhole Industry, and the local dealer.\nif he is new and inexperienced, is\n1 very liable to stub his toe on this\ni stumbling block. However, the wise\ndealer sells h.s products to a cub\ni tomcr and the old car can then bo\nr oonslderetl on a satisfactory basis.\nSome of tho largest manufacturers\nat the present time ar\u00a9 giving much\ntime and study to tho \"used oar\u201d\nproblem, and it is only a matter of\na short time until some method will\nl\u00bbe worked out to assist the dealer in\nhandling this situation.\nOne of the greatest contributing\nr factors to the remarkable growth of\ni the motor car Industry in recent\ni years ho\u00a9 been the formation of fl\nnance corporations to take car e of\n\u2018\u2019times sales,\" thus making it pos-\nOc Casper 9unHap Cribune\nsible for the dealer to sell cars on\ntho monthly payment plan. This\nWE MANUFACTURE THE\nFOR DODGE CjKR S\nState Distributors For\nGRUSS AIR SPRINGS\nand\nWILL SOLID TRUCK TIRE ADAPTERS\nDealer Agencies Solicited\nHave Largest Spring Stock in Wyoming\u2014ls We Havn\u2019t Your Spring\nWe Can Make It\nDISC AND WIRE WHEEL EXPERTS\nCASPER SPRING COMPANY\n328 W. Midwest Casper, Wyoming Phone 1369\nI plan was first inaugurated by the\nGeneral Motors company to facili- 1\ntat\u00a9 the distribution of Its own prod- 1\nuct r but ftinc\u00a9 has beooms an tnsti- I\ntution in Itself, until now \u00a9wry lo- f\noallty has its finance corporations,\neach soliciting business from the 1\nmore reliable and responsible deal- j\nA few motor companies have\nmad\u00a9 price reductions in bringing\nout the 1924 models* but taken as a 1\nwhole manufacturers, at present,\nare offering more value for the\nmoney than ever before in tho his-\nItory of th\u00ae industry.\nNearly every make of car manu\nfactured In the United States Is rep-\nresented among Casper dealers, and\nwhile each dealer reports having had\na most successful season during I\n1923, they are all planning and Ipok- I\nIng forward to a bigger and greater\nseason during 1924.\nSpeaking for the Nash Casper Mo-\ntor company, in which I am asso\nciated with W. I. Ti-elier. I do not\nhesitate to state that w\u00a9 have been\nmere than pleased with our Nash\nand Peerless sales during 19*3. and\njudging from present business con- I\nditions in (Y\u00bbsper. 1924 sales should\nbe even better.\nNash has ad<?ed to its line of beau\ntiful closed cars, a Victoria coupe,\nwhich leaves nothing to l\u00bbe desired\nin completeness of design and work\nmanship. This new model Victoria\nwill be shown for tho first time in\nI Casper at the Auto Show next week,\nalong w.th other Nash closed\nI models.\nWhile w\u00a9 have had no definite fn\nformation from tho Nash factory, f\nI we do not feel that there will be any\nchange in prices of Nash cars, and\n!as our 1924 mode's are already out. i\nIwe feel positive there will be no,\nI further change in models. It la this*\npolicy of standardization which\nliarscterlsee tho entire Nash insti\ntution. that has lead to th\u00a9 popular\nj opinion among owners, that \u201cNash\nJxnds th\u00a9 World in Motor Car\nValue.\u201d\nTH\u00abDE APPRECIATION\nVOIGEB IN CASPER BY\nSTUDEBAKER AGENCY\ni\n(By Studebaker Sales and Service)\nWe are taking thia opportunity to\nthank our many friends for the\nlarge volume ot Studebaker* busi\nness. which has been rapidly in-\nI creasing since our initial step in the\nagency on May 1.\nIt is a pleasure to announce that\n1 we have a complete line of Stude\nbaker parts In transit, and that wo\n1 will be able to guarantee the very\nbest of aervice.\nThe 1924 model Studebaker cars\nwill continue In production without\nchange throughout the coming win- I.\nter and 1924 season. They ar\u00a9 not\nand will not be equipped with four\nwheel brakes.\nWe have a complete line of 1924\nmodels on our floor, which we be\nlieve speak for themselves. Com\u00a9\ntn and be convinced.\nCasper Auto Top Shop\n633 South Center Phone 1084-R\nFOR SERVICE AND QUALITY WORK\nWe make tops, seat covers, radiator covers .also auto\ncushings, general upholstery\nAUTOMILE PAINTING A SPECIALTY\n\u201cThe Best Automobiles go\nWrong Sometimes\u201d\nWe Are Thoroughly Prepared to Put Them on Their\nFeet Again\nMaxwell Chalmers\nWills St. Claire\nThese three' cars are specialties with us as every me\nchanic in our shop is thoroughly experienced in re\npairing and service on these machines.\nUnited Auto Service Co.\n221 W. Yellowstone Phone 1545\n\u201cChubb\u201d Steel\u2014F. C. Norris\u2014Duff Quinn\nJack Baldauf\nPAGE THREE","height":"18356","width":"15208"}}
